Last Broadcast Date: Wed 19 May 2010
Personal stories behind the news from all over the world. With Matthew Bannister. Rory Stewart - a week in the life of a new British MP Rory Stewart Rory Stewart has been a soldier, a diplomat and a bestselling author. He was once governor of a province in post war Iraq and walked six thousand miles across Asia - relying solely on the hospitality of people he met. He's now Member of Parliament for Penrith and the Border - which covers an area of North West England. In today's special programme he gives his very personal view of what it's like to become a new MP at a time of economic and political uncertainty. Show less